  "source": "claude-advisor",
  "edge_hypothesis": "VWAP_D represents institutional volume-weighted fair value. CCI measures statistical deviation from a moving average. When BOTH indicators agree that price is overextended (close below VWAP AND CCI oversold below -100), two independent mean-reversion forces converge — volume-based fair value pull AND statistical mean pull. In ranging markets (CHOP > 50), this double-confirmation should produce higher-conviction mean-reversion entries than CCI alone (CCI Chop Fade v2 PF=1.255). VWAP_D has NEVER been tested in any strategy — this is first-contact with volume-weighted pricing as a signal component.",
